summary: Real life is a funny thing, you know. In real life, saying the right thing at the right moment is beyond crucial. So crucial, in...
body:
Real life is a funny thing, you know. In real life, saying the right thing at the right moment is beyond crucial. So crucial, in fact, that most of us start to hesitate, for fear of saying the wrong thing at the wrong time. But lately what I’ve begun to fear more than that is letting that moment pass without saying anything.

There is a time for silence. There is a time waiting your turn. But if you know how you feel, and you clearly know what you need to say, you’ll know it.

I don’t think you should wait, I think you should speak now.

summary: GUYS
body:
GUYS

2014: “I’ve spent my whole life trying to put it into words.”

2017: “Call it what you want”


Now that she’s found her true love she cares less about finding the right words to explain/validate her feelings. Now that she has Joe, she found her happily ever after and words are no longer necessary. She no longer cares how others preceive her relationship because it’s real to them and that’s all that matters.


Brb I need to go cry for a week.



@taylorswift

summary: Speak Now coming out 8 years ago today makes me feel old af and super emotional. I remember that day like it was yesterday. I...
body: Speak Now coming out 8 years ago today makes me feel old af and super emotional. I remember that day like it was yesterday. I was hanging out with my friends and I asked them to bring me to target after we ate at this really good buffet and omg I was soooo excited to get the Target version of Speak Now! That was the first time I bought a Taylor Swift album on its release date. My friends knew how excited I was to get it and they were so supportive and let me play it in the car on the way home 😍 Then shortly after I purchased my first car, I drove my bff at the time to a mall BLASTING Speak Now the whole time! That was the soundtrack to the rest of that school year honestly. I think that’s when I realized how much I love Taylor ❤️ so happy 8 years Speak Now! I am going to blast it on the way to work and pretend I’m still that 16 (going on 17) year old girl!

summary: 1989 Album
title: 1989 Album
body: I am so excited about the release of 1989. I have had the album on repeat for hours now and my favourite song so far is Blank Space. The album is so different from RED. It sounds more pop in style and there is such a sense of happiness in both the music and lyrics. I also love that her handwriting is on the booklet because it makes it feel so much more personal. It really feels like she has put everything into this album and I could not be happier for her right now.
